    <description>Pangea is the prehistoric one continent world.  Each time you open Tribes of Pangea, you will create a new one-continent world to explore.  Players seed the world with unknown resources to explore and use them to either build their own infrastructure, or to conquer opponent tribes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players win by defeating all opponent tribes in Pangea.  Victory is usually reached with a balanced strategy of war, economy, and fame.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn your tribe is not starving, you get more population, which means you can gather more resources, build more infrastructure, and build more armies with which to gain control of even more resources... until Pangea is yours.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game typically takes between 3 and 5 hours.  While only having an 11 page rule book, the game does have some considerable learning curve.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game features include: &amp;#10;  * a random setup, to ensure a new game every time you play&amp;#10;  * a battle resolution table to facilitate rolling dice for battles&amp;#10;  * 3 types of military units, melee, ranged, and magic&amp;#10;  * buildings and resources that can upgrade military units&amp;#10;  * a system of fame and bribing, if you decide that war isn't going to work for you!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2-6 players, ages 12 and up&amp;#10;Contents: 56 building counters, 36 resource counters, 180 military counters, 5 dice, 6 tribe cards, 1 battle resolution table, 36 continent and ocean hexes, 18 roads, 66 counting chip counters, 11 page rule book, 6 page reference almanac.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
